.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-29 relay\-based groups. Groups are identified by a string
restricted to \f(CW\*(C`a\-z0\-9\-_\*(C'\fR and belong to a specific relay. Group state
is managed through moderation events (kinds 9000\-9009) and user events
(kinds 9021\-9022). Group metadata is published as addressable events
(kinds 39000\-39003) signed by the relay.
.PP
All user and moderation events MUST include an \f(CW\*(C`h\*(C'\fR tag with the group
id. Group metadata events use a \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag instead.
.PP
To store a user\*(Aqs list of groups, use a kind 10009 Net::Nostr::List
with \f(CW\*(C`group\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`r\*(C'\fR tags per NIP\-51:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::List;
\&
\&    my $groups = Net::Nostr::List\->new(kind => 10009);
\&    $groups\->add(\*(Aqgroup\*(Aq, "groups.nostr.com\*(Aqpizza", \*(Aqwss://groups.nostr.com\*(Aq, \*(AqPizza Lovers\*(Aq);
\&    $groups\->add(\*(Aqr\*(Aq, \*(Aqwss://groups.nostr.com\*(Aq);
\&    my $event = $groups\->to_event(pubkey => $key\->pubkey_hex);
.Ve
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS parse_id
.IX Subsection "parse_id"
.Vb 2
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::Group\->parse_id("groups.nostr.com\*(Aqpizza");
\&    # { host => \*(Aqgroups.nostr.com\*(Aq, group_id => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq }
\&
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::Group\->parse_id("groups.nostr.com");
\&    # { host => \*(Aqgroups.nostr.com\*(Aq, group_id => \*(Aq_\*(Aq }
.Ve
.PP
Parses a group identifier string in \f(CW\*(C`<host>\*(Aq<group\-id>\*(C'\fR format.
If only a host is given (no \f(CW\*(C`\*(Aq\*(C'\fR), infers \f(CW\*(C`_\*(C'\fR as the group id per
NIP\-29. Croaks if the group id contains invalid characters.
.SS format_id
.IX Subsection "format_id"
.Vb 5
\&    my $id = Net::Nostr::Group\->format_id(
\&        host     => \*(Aqgroups.nostr.com\*(Aq,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&    # "groups.nostr.com\*(Aqpizza"
.Ve
.PP
Formats a group identifier string from host and group_id components.
.SS validate_group_id
.IX Subsection "validate_group_id"
.Vb 2
\&    Net::Nostr::Group\->validate_group_id(\*(Aqmy\-group\*(Aq);  # 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Group\->validate_group_id(\*(AqNOPE\*(Aq);      # 0
.Ve
.PP
Returns true if the group id matches the allowed character set
\&\f(CW\*(C`a\-z0\-9\-_\*(C'\fR.
.SS put_user
.IX Subsection "put_user"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->put_user(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&        target   => $user_pubkey,
\&        roles    => [\*(Aqadmin\*(Aq, \*(Aqmoderator\*(Aq],  # optional
\&        reason   => \*(Aqpromoted\*(Aq,              # optional
\&        previous => [\*(Aqabcd1234\*(Aq],            # optional timeline refs
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 9000 moderation event to add a user to the group or
update their roles. The \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag contains the target pubkey followed
by any role strings.
.SS remove_user
.IX Subsection "remove_user"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->remove_user(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&        target   => $user_pubkey,
\&        reason   => \*(Aqspamming\*(Aq,  # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 9001 moderation event to remove a user from the group.
.PP
All user and moderation event builders (\f(CW\*(C`put_user\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`remove_user\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`edit_metadata\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`delete_event\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`create_group\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`delete_group\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`create_invite\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`join_request\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`leave_request\*(C'\fR) accept an optional
\&\f(CW\*(C`previous\*(C'\fR parameter for timeline references. See \f(CW\*(C`put_user\*(C'\fR for an
example.
.SS edit_metadata
.IX Subsection "edit_metadata"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->edit_metadata(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,
\&        group_id     => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&        name         => \*(AqPizza Lovers\*(Aq,       # optional
\&        picture      => \*(Aqhttps://pic.url\*(Aq,    # optional
\&        about        => \*(Aqdescription\*(Aq,        # optional
\&        private      => 1,                    # optional flag
\&        restricted   => 1,                    # optional flag
\&        hidden       => 1,                    # optional flag
\&        closed       => 1,                    # optional flag
\&        unrestricted => 1,                    # optional flag
\&        open         => 1,                    # optional flag
\&        visible      => 1,                    # optional flag
\&        public       => 1,                    # optional flag
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 9002 moderation event to update group metadata. Metadata
fields become tags. Boolean flags become single\-element tags when true.
.SS delete_event
.IX Subsection "delete_event"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->delete_event(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&        event_id => $event_id_hex,
\&        reason   => \*(Aqspam content\*(Aq,  # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 9005 moderation event to delete an event from the group.
.SS create_group
.IX Subsection "create_group"
.Vb 4
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->create_group(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqnew\-group\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 9007 event requesting the relay to create a new group.
.SS delete_group
.IX Subsection "delete_group"
.Vb 5
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->delete_group(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqold\-group\*(Aq,
\&        reason   => \*(Aqinactive\*(Aq,  # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 9008 event requesting the relay to delete a group.
.SS create_invite
.IX Subsection "create_invite"
.Vb 5
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->create_invite(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&        code     => \*(Aqsecret\-code\-123\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 9009 event with an invite code for the group.
.SS join_request
.IX Subsection "join_request"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->join_request(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&        reason   => \*(AqI love pizza\*(Aq,   # optional
\&        code     => \*(Aqinvite\-abc\*(Aq,     # optional invite code
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 9021 join request event. The optional \f(CW\*(C`code\*(C'\fR tag can
be used with invite codes created by \f(CW\*(C`create_invite\*(C'\fR.
.SS leave_request
.IX Subsection "leave_request"
.Vb 5
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->leave_request(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&        reason   => \*(Aqmoving on\*(Aq,  # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 9022 leave request event.
.SS metadata
.IX Subsection "metadata"
.Vb 11
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->metadata(
\&        pubkey     => $relay_pubkey,
\&        group_id   => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&        name       => \*(AqPizza Lovers\*(Aq,
\&        picture    => \*(Aqhttps://pizza.com/pizza.png\*(Aq,
\&        about      => \*(Aqa group for pizza fans\*(Aq,
\&        private    => 1,    # only members can read
\&        restricted => 1,    # only members can write
\&        hidden     => 1,    # hide metadata from non\-members
\&        closed     => 1,    # ignore join requests
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 39000 addressable event describing group metadata.
This event should be signed by the relay\*(Aqs master key. Uses a \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR
tag (not \f(CW\*(C`h\*(C'\fR) with the group id.
.SS admins
.IX Subsection "admins"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->admins(
\&        pubkey   => $relay_pubkey,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&        content  => \*(Aqadmin list\*(Aq,  # optional
\&        members  => [
\&            { pubkey => $pk, roles => [\*(Aqadmin\*(Aq] },
\&        ],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 39001 addressable event listing group admins with roles.
.SS members
.IX Subsection "members"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->members(
\&        pubkey   => $relay_pubkey,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&        content  => \*(Aqmember list\*(Aq,  # optional
\&        members  => [$pk1, $pk2],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 39002 addressable event listing group members.
.SS roles
.IX Subsection "roles"
.Vb 9
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Group\->roles(
\&        pubkey   => $relay_pubkey,
\&        group_id => \*(Aqpizza\*(Aq,
\&        content  => \*(Aqrole definitions\*(Aq,  # optional
\&        roles    => [
\&            { name => \*(Aqadmin\*(Aq, description => \*(Aqfull control\*(Aq },
\&            { name => \*(Aqmoderator\*(Aq },
\&        ],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 39003 addressable event listing supported roles.
.SS metadata_from_event
.IX Subsection "metadata_from_event"
.Vb 3
\&    my $meta = Net::Nostr::Group\->metadata_from_event($event);
\&    # { group_id => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, name => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, picture => \*(Aq...\*(Aq,
\&    #   about => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, private => 1, closed => 1 }
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 39000 event. Returns a hashref with group metadata.
Boolean flags (\f(CW\*(C`private\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`restricted\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`hidden\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`closed\*(C'\fR) are
set to 1 when present. Croaks if the event is not kind 39000.
.SS admins_from_event
.IX Subsection "admins_from_event"
.Vb 2
\&    my $result = Net::Nostr::Group\->admins_from_event($event);
\&    # { group_id => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, admins => [{ pubkey => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, roles => [...] }] }
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 39001 event. Returns a hashref with group_id and an
arrayref of admin entries. Croaks if the event is not kind 39001.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    for my $admin (@{$result\->{admins}}) {
\&        say "$admin\->{pubkey}: " . join(\*(Aq, \*(Aq, @{$admin\->{roles}});
\&    }
.Ve
.SS members_from_event
.IX Subsection "members_from_event"
.Vb 2
\&    my $result = Net::Nostr::Group\->members_from_event($event);
\&    # { group_id => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, members => [$pk1, $pk2] }
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 39002 event. Returns a hashref with group_id and an
arrayref of member pubkeys. Croaks if the event is not kind 39002.
.SS roles_from_event
.IX Subsection "roles_from_event"
.Vb 2
\&    my $result = Net::Nostr::Group\->roles_from_event($event);
\&    # { group_id => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, roles => [{ name => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, description => \*(Aq...\*(Aq }] }
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 39003 event. Returns a hashref with group_id and an
arrayref of role definitions. Croaks if the event is not kind 39003.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    for my $role (@{$result\->{roles}}) {
\&        say "$role\->{name}: $role\->{description}";
\&    }
.Ve
.SS group_id_from_event
.IX Subsection "group_id_from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $gid = Net::Nostr::Group\->group_id_from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Extracts the group id from an event\*(Aqs \f(CW\*(C`h\*(C'\fR tag (user/moderation events)
or \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag (metadata events). If both tags are present, the \f(CW\*(C`h\*(C'\fR tag
takes priority. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if neither is found.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $gid = Net::Nostr::Group\->group_id_from_event($join_event);
\&    say "Group: $gid";
.Ve
